This paper is about improving speech recognition using neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper explores the effects of experimental variables, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
